WEST NILE VIRUS UPDATE 2003 - CANADA (10)
*****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date Thu 17 Jul 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Health Canada, West Nile Virus Surveillance, Thu 17 Jul 2003 [edited]
<http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/pphb-dgspsp/wnv-vwn/pdf_sr-rs/2003/situation_report_071703_db.pdf>

West Nile virus surveillance data as of Thu 17 Jul 2003
-------------------------------------------------------
Human
-----
No confirmed reports
Equines
-------
No confirmed reports
Mosquitoes
----------
The Ministry of Health and Long-Term Care (MOHLTC) has been advised that as
of Tue 15 Jul 2003 the report of one West Nile virus positive mosquito
pool, posted on 24 Jun 2003, is incorrect. The sample taken 18 Jun 2003,
which was tested by a private laboratory, has -- upon further confirmatory
testing -- has proven negative for West Nile virus.
Wild Birds
----------
Test results by province:
Province / No. submitted for testing / No.tested / No. confirmed positive
Newfoundland and Labrador / 30 / 29 / 0
Prince Edward Island / 140 / 134 / 0
Nova Scotia / 289 / 281 / 0
New Brunswick / 241 / 238 / 0
Quebec / 776 / 710 / 2
Ontario / 945 / 833 / 23
Manitoba / 711 / 637 / 33
Saskatchewan / 606 / 483 / 2
Alberta / 274 / 250 / 2
British Columbia / 1193 / 1167 / 0
Yukon / 7 / 6 / 0
Northwest Territories / 7 / 7 / 0
Nunavut / 1 / 1 / 0
The totals for Canada for 2003 so far are 5219 birds submitted for testing,
4786 birds tested, and 62 confirmed West Nile virus positive. In addition
there were 1094 sightings of dead birds recorded. [This represents an
increase of 2018 birds tested and 37 more birds confirmed positive since
the last update on 30 Jun 2003. - Mod.CP]
